g.text: fTheta = 15.00 => theta angle of trapezoid axis
fPhi = 30.00 => phi angle of trapezoid axis
fH1 = 20.00 => half length in y at -fDz
fAlpha1 = 0.00 => angle between centers of x edges and y axis at -fDz
fBl1 = 10.00 => half length in x at -dZ and y=-fH1
fTl1 = 15.00 => half length in x at -dZ and y=+fH1
fH2 = 20.00 => half length in y at +fDz
fBl2 = 10.00 => half length in x at +dZ and y=-fH1
fTl2 = 15.00 => half length in x at +dZ and y=+fH1
fAlpha2 = 0.00 => angle between centers of x edges and y axis at +fDz
Execute: gtra(iaxis, ndiv, start, step) to divide this.
----- NDIV must be a positive integer
----- START must be a valid axis offset within shape range on divided axis
----- STEP is the division step. START+NDIV*STEP must be in range also
----- If START and STEP are omitted, all range of the axis will be divided
